The image we see will be coming from the
onboard microscope.

56
00:07:45.950 --> 00:07:49.450
Sorry. I have to go now.

57
00:07:56.460 --> 00:08:02.045
The sound waves are physical and at

58
00:08:02.069 --> 00:08:08.617
different frequencies they make different

59
00:08:08.641 --> 00:08:13.920
patterns Olivia. can you help me out?

60
00:08:14.080 --> 00:08:17.580
There we go.

61
00:08:19.440 --> 00:08:22.356
Are they really eating the sun?

62
00:08:22.380 --> 00:08:23.956
The space dots?

63
00:08:23.980 --> 00:08:26.316
That is a great question. Rekha.

64
00:08:26.340 --> 00:08:29.376
And I'D be curious what your parents think
about that.

65
00:08:29.400 --> 00:08:31.156
I'm not sure It should come from me.

66
00:08:31.180 --> 00:08:34.680
Hey. who wants to play a game of...

67
00:08:34.880 --> 00:08:36.036
Vegas Lava?

68
00:08:36.060 --> 00:08:37.156
Lava!

69
00:08:37.180 --> 00:08:37.956
Lava!

70
00:08:37.980 --> 00:08:38.437
Lava!

71
00:08:38.461 --> 00:08:41.916
What is the speed-up line. Olivia?

72
00:08:41.940 --> 00:08:44.496
Uh... It's melting your hands. Olivia!

73
00:08:44.520 --> 00:08:46.876
186.000 miles per second!

74
00:08:46.900 --> 00:08:47.256
Oh!

75
00:08:47.280 --> 00:08:48.756
Give her a round of applause.

76
00:08:48.780 --> 00:08:50.876
That is awesome.

77
00:08:50.900 --> 00:08:53.656
What is the Petrova Line?

78
00:08:53.680 --> 00:08:55.116
Pass.

79
00:08:55.140 --> 00:08:58.576
You can't pass.

80
00:08:58.600 --> 00:08:59.177
Lava!

81
00:08:59.201 --> 00:09:00.236
Lava!

82
00:09:00.260 --> 00:09:00.837
Lava!

83
00:09:00.861 --> 00:09:01.396
Lava!

84
00:09:01.420 --> 00:09:08.060
Two years ago. a radio telescope
enthusiast named Marina Petrova.

85
00:09:09.060 --> 00:09:13.880
she noticed that there was a streak of
infrared light from the sun to Venus.

86
00:09:14.280 --> 00:09:17.336
And that is now known
as the Petrova Line.

87
00:09:17.360 --> 00:09:18.376
That's It.

88
00:09:18.400 --> 00:09:19.856
That's the dots?

89
00:09:19.880 --> 00:09:20.956
They think so.

90
00:09:20.980 --> 00:09:24.480
What dots?

91
00:09:25.910 --> 00:09:27.746
These dots.

92
00:09:27.770 --> 00:09:31.610
They sent a probe up to the Petrova Line.
and this is what they found.

93
00:09:33.370 --> 00:09:36.826
Are they eating the sun?

94
00:09:36.850 --> 00:09:40.026
They seem to be dimming the sun.

95
00:09:40.050 --> 00:09:43.550
A tiny. teeny. weeny little bit.

96
00:09:43.730 --> 00:09:45.146
So no big whoop.

97
00:09:45.170 --> 00:09:46.866
It's a small whoop.

98
00:09:46.890 --> 00:09:48.986
It's a small to medium whoop.

99
00:09:49.010 --> 00:09:57.010
Over the next 30 years. the Earth could
cool maybe 10 to 15 degrees.

100
00:09:58.910 --> 00:10:00.347
So It is a big whoop.

101
00:10:00.371 --> 00:10:02.630
I heard that all the crops will die.

102
00:10:02.654 --> 00:10:06.230
the economy will free fall. and
half the Earth will die of starvation.

103
00:10:07.410 --> 00:10:10.006
Well... We're all gonna die.

104
00:10:10.030 --> 00:10:11.186
Yeah. that's true.

105
00:10:11.210 --> 00:10:12.306
You're forgetting something.

106
00:10:12.330 --> 00:10:15.206
Guys. guys. that's if that were to happen.

107
00:10:15.230 --> 00:10:15.906
Right?

108
00:10:15.930 --> 00:10:17.646
They're gonna figure this out.

109
00:10:17.670 --> 00:10:18.606
Right now.

110
00:10:18.630 --> 00:10:23.510
The best minds in the entire world are on
It.

111
00:10:40.500 --> 00:10:44.880
With no way to hold my head and my skin
didn't hurt.

112
00:10:48.030 --> 00:10:50.346
Good morning. Dr. Grace.

113
00:10:50.370 --> 00:10:53.870
And the beer I had for breakfast wasn't
bad.

114
00:10:53.950 --> 00:10:57.450
So I had one more for dessert.

115
00:11:02.120 --> 00:11:06.034
Then I headed back for
home and somewhere

116
00:11:06.058 --> 00:11:09.558
