117
00:11:13.950 --> 00:11:19.470
And It echoed through the canyons like the
disappearing dream.

118
00:11:19.910 --> 00:11:23.410
Yesterday.

119
00:11:23.710 --> 00:11:31.710
On the Sunday morning sidewalks wishing.
Lord. that I was stoned.

120
00:11:35.930 --> 00:11:43.930
Cause there's something in a Sunday that
makes a body feel alone.

121
00:11:46.110 --> 00:11:51.130
There's nothing short of dying.

122
00:11:53.970 --> 00:11:57.470
Half as lonesome as It sounds.

123
00:12:00.150 --> 00:12:04.190
On the sleeping city sidewalks.

124
00:12:05.990 --> 00:12:09.490
Sunday morning coming...

125
00:12:32.270 --> 00:12:35.386
Knock. knock.

126
00:12:35.410 --> 00:12:36.586
Who's there?

127
00:12:36.610 --> 00:12:37.986
Not good at jokes.

128
00:12:38.010 --> 00:12:41.510
Not good at jokes who?

129
00:12:43.140 --> 00:12:46.640
Dr. Grace.

130
00:12:46.780 --> 00:12:47.576
Maybe.

131
00:12:47.600 --> 00:12:49.776
Eva Stratton with the
Petrova Task Force.

132
00:12:49.800 --> 00:12:51.516
I need your help.

133
00:12:51.540 --> 00:12:52.296
Me.

134
00:12:52.320 --> 00:12:55.820
Did you write this?

135
00:12:56.820 --> 00:12:57.536
Oh.

136
00:12:57.560 --> 00:12:59.456
I'm interested in this section here.

137
00:12:59.480 --> 00:13:01.016
Page 31.

138
00:13:01.040 --> 00:13:03.256
The Goldilocks Zone is for idiots.

139
00:13:03.280 --> 00:13:05.956
Why everyone is wrong about life.

140
00:13:05.980 --> 00:13:07.676
That was a long time ago.

141
00:13:07.700 --> 00:13:08.916
Do you stand by what you wrote?

142
00:13:08.940 --> 00:13:11.596
I was fired for standing by what I wrote.

143
00:13:11.620 --> 00:13:15.597
You were fired for calling the leading
scholar in your field a stacker.

144
00:13:15.621 --> 00:13:16.775
You were fired for delivering waste of

145
00:13:16.799 --> 00:13:18.856
carbon at the UNESCO
conference in Denmark.

146
00:13:18.880 --> 00:13:21.276
You heard about that. huh?

147
00:13:21.300 --> 00:13:27.060
Look. I don't know what this is.
but I think that's lava.

148
00:13:27.600 --> 00:13:28.356
It's not.

149
00:13:28.380 --> 00:13:29.536
Okay.

150
00:13:29.560 --> 00:13:31.358
No one in your field wants anything to do

151
00:13:31.382 --> 00:13:33.137
with you because you
refuse to back down

152
00:13:33.161 --> 00:13:34.977
from a very unpopular
view and I can give

153
00:13:35.001 --> 00:13:36.716
you a chance to prove them all wrong.

154
00:13:36.740 --> 00:13:38.556
That's Kevin Noe running.

155
00:13:38.580 --> 00:13:40.076
I'm not.

156
00:13:40.100 --> 00:13:42.516
Joke's on them because
I don't even care.

157
00:13:42.540 --> 00:13:44.416
So...

158
00:13:44.440 --> 00:13:45.736
I think you do care.

159
00:13:45.760 --> 00:13:47.536
You're just running away because you're
scared.

160
00:13:47.560 --> 00:13:50.756
No. no. no.

161
00:13:50.780 --> 00:13:54.280
Do you still believe water is unnecessary
for life to evolve?

162
00:13:54.380 --> 00:13:55.496
Uh...

163
00:13:55.520 --> 00:13:59.240
Look. there is nothing magical about
hydrogen and oxygen.

164
00:13:59.560 --> 00:14:01.316
Water is required for life on Earth.

165
00:14:01.340 --> 00:14:03.039
Sure. but a completely different planet

166
00:14:03.063 --> 00:14:04.956
might have completely
different conditions.

167
00:14:04.980 --> 00:14:06.896
I don't know why that
makes me such a nut.

168
00:14:06.920 --> 00:14:09.936
I need you to come with us.

169
00:14:09.960 --> 00:14:11.356
Sorry. I didn't catch your name.

170
00:14:11.380 --> 00:14:11.537
Carl.

171
00:14:11.561 --> 00:14:12.396
Hi.

172
00:14:12.420 --> 00:14:13.276
Carl. hi.

173
00:14:13.300 --> 00:14:14.771
Dr. Grace. for trouble line samples

174
00:14:14.795 --> 00:14:16.437
splashed down last night. I want you to

175
00:14:16.461 --> 00:14:18.756
tell me what they are. how they work.

176
00:14:18.780 --> 00:14:21.596
I am a teacher at
Grover Cleveland Middle.

177
00:14:21.620 --> 00:14:23.736
And you have a doctorate in molecular
biology.

178
00:14:23.760 --> 00:14:25.476
And I ride a bike to work.

179
00:14:25.500 --> 00:14:29.697
And. uh. It's not for exercise.
so I'm sure there are thousands of other

180
00:14:29.721 --> 00:14:31.696
people... It survives on
the surface of the sun.

181
00:14:31.720 --> 00:14:35.220
Does that sound like a water-based life
form to you?

182
00:14:40.940 --> 00:14:42.796
The sun's really dying. isn't It?

183
00:14:42.820 --> 00:14:46.320
Yeah.

184
00:14:48.330 --> 00:14:50.126
Is all of this...

185
00:14:50.150 --> 00:14:52.606
necessary?

186
00:14:52.630 --> 00:14:54.046
Yes.

187
00:14:54.070 --> 00:14:56.966
Please analyze the patrol sample.

188
00:14:56.990 --> 00:14:58.286
Um...

189
00:14:58.310 --> 00:14:59.266
Just one thing.

190
00:14:59.290 --> 00:15:00.926
The entire room is filled with argon.

191
00:15:00.950 --> 00:15:03.786
Just try not to rip your suit.

192
00:15:03.810 --> 00:15:06.886
Uh...

193
00:15:06.910 --> 00:15:08.266
Am I expendable?

194
00:15:08.290 --> 00:15:09.626
Is that why you want me?

195
00:15:09.650 --> 00:15:11.386
That's not the only reason.

196
00:15:11.410 --> 00:15:14.910
It's almost like you don't care if I die.

197
00:15:18.000 --> 00:15:21.176
Hold on. you have to talk about It?

198
00:15:21.200 --> 00:15:25.320
The consensus here is that It would be
preferable if you did not die.

199
00:15:26.660 --> 00:15:30.160
Thanks. guys.

200
00:15:35.340 --> 00:15:38.840
Oh.

201
00:15:42.090 --> 00:15:45.590
Welcome to Earth.

202
00:15:58.560 --> 00:16:00.696
Are they alive?

203
00:16:00.720 --> 00:16:02.276
They're moving.

204
00:16:02.300 --> 00:16:03.756
So they're alive.

205
00:16:03.780 --> 00:16:05.877
They're mov... Yes. they're moving.
but they're...

206
00:16:05.901 --> 00:16:07.516
That could be for many reasons.

207
00:16:07.540 --> 00:16:08.856
I'm... What are they made of?

208
00:16:08.880 --> 00:16:09.857
It's gonna take a long ti...

209
00:16:09.881 --> 00:16:13.157
It took. like. 200 years to figure out how
bacteria work. so...

210
00:16:13.181 --> 00:16:16.681
Please do It faster.

211
00:16:16.920 --> 00:16:20.420
I'm just going through the whole light
spectrum here.

212
00:16:20.600 --> 00:16:23.456
Wow!

213
00:16:23.480 --> 00:16:26.980
You're not gonna believe this.

214
00:16:28.120 --> 00:16:31.620
Nothing happened.

215
00:16:34.240 --> 00:16:37.740
I can't see into these buggers.

216
00:16:38.980 --> 00:16:40.056
Amazing.

217
00:16:40.080 --> 00:16:44.020
X-rays. microwaves. gamma rays.
visible light.

218
00:16:44.240 --> 00:16:46.856
Nothing.

219
00:16:46.880 --> 00:16:48.156
Ooh. ooh. ooh. ooh.

220
00:16:48.180 --> 00:16:51.680
I've been dying to do this all day.

221
00:17:07.210 --> 00:17:08.126
It's a cell!

222
00:17:08.150 --> 00:17:09.026
It's a cell?

223
00:17:09.050 --> 00:17:11.066
Wake up. It's a cell!

224
00:17:11.090 --> 00:17:13.406
It's a tiny alien cell.

225
00:17:13.430 --> 00:17:14.366
Guys.

226
00:17:14.390 --> 00:17:16.506
I've lost... Guys!

227
00:17:16.530 --> 00:17:19.406
This is first contact...

228
00:17:19.430 --> 00:17:22.546
with life... ...outside of the...

229
00:17:22.570 --> 00:17:24.586
Uh-oh.

230
00:17:24.610 --> 00:17:26.486
Oh. It died.

231
00:17:26.510 --> 00:17:28.326
What?

232
00:17:28.350 --> 00:17:29.926
This is great news.

233
00:17:29.950 --> 00:17:33.450
Now we can find out
what they're made of.

234
00:17:34.770 --> 00:17:38.270
You guys fired up?

235
00:17:39.830 --> 00:17:41.446
Yes!

236
00:17:41.470 --> 00:17:43.786
Right?

237
00:17:43.810 --> 00:17:46.046
Carbon.

238
00:17:46.070 --> 00:17:49.570
Oxygen.

239
00:17:49.850 --> 00:17:51.646
Hydrogen.

240
00:17:51.670 --> 00:17:55.170
Oh.

241
00:18:07.090 --> 00:18:10.590
It's made...

242
00:18:11.590 --> 00:18:15.090
almost entirely...

243
00:18:15.270 --> 00:18:18.770
of water.

244
00:18:26.190 --> 00:18:29.690
All right.

245
00:18:30.420 --> 00:18:33.536
Sorry if I overreacted in there.

246
00:18:33.560 --> 00:18:37.740
Just realizing I was wrong about the only
original idea I ever had.

247
00:18:38.080 --> 00:18:38.356
Yeah.

248
00:18:38.380 --> 00:18:39.776
What else did you learn?

249
00:18:39.800 --> 00:18:42.836
They give off infrared light when they
move.

250
00:18:42.860 --> 00:18:43.957
Like. so much.

251
00:18:43.981 --> 00:18:45.956
I don't know how they store all that
energy.

252
00:18:45.980 --> 00:18:50.560
But... their wavelength is
exactly the Petrova frequency.

253
00:18:51.120 --> 00:18:52.636
Their light is how they move?

254
00:18:52.660 --> 00:18:56.160
Yeah. they consume the sun's energy and
then they expel It for propulsion.

255
00:18:56.640 --> 00:19:00.140
They toot to scoot. basically.

256
00:19:00.580 --> 00:19:04.080
Why did It go to Venus?

257
00:19:04.160 --> 00:19:07.136
I don't know.

258
00:19:07.160 --> 00:19:07.617
Okay.

259
00:19:07.641 --> 00:19:08.916
We'll tell you.

260
00:19:08.940 --> 00:19:09.736
What?

261
00:19:09.760 --> 00:19:14.040
I have 347 other biologists in 21
countries mobilizing as we speak.

262
00:19:14.180 --> 00:19:15.697
So. thank you for your help.

263
00:19:15.721 --> 00:19:16.956
I'm glad you didn't die.

264
00:19:16.980 --> 00:19:20.480
Let's pack this up.

265
00:19:23.020 --> 00:19:24.676
That's It?

266
00:19:24.700 --> 00:19:25.616
That's It. Carl?

267
00:19:25.640 --> 00:19:26.396
Talk to her.

268
00:19:26.420 --> 00:19:28.116
You just... you're taking all this stuff?

269
00:19:28.140 --> 00:19:29.454
At the school you said there were

270
00:19:29.478 --> 00:19:31.447
thousands of people
more qualified than you. so.

271
00:19:31.471 --> 00:19:31.777
...

272
00:19:31.801 --> 00:19:32.856
I was being modest.

273
00:19:32.880 --> 00:19:33.756
I don't need modest.

274
00:19:33.780 --> 00:19:35.313
I need people who think they're right

275
00:19:35.337 --> 00:19:37.076
when everyone else
thinks they're wrong.

276
00:19:37.100 --> 00:19:38.716
I need people who piss other people off.

277
00:19:38.740 --> 00:19:39.436
That's me.

278
00:19:39.460 --> 00:19:41.636
